To this class Keller and Holder assign B Bernensis 363, probably the oldest of all extant MSS. of Horace, written by an Irish monk in the eighth or ninth century, as is proved by some Irish glosses in the margin. Unfortunately it ends at Sat. i. 134, thus including the Ars Poelz'ca (ex- cept vv. 440—476), but omitting all the Epistles.
